#compdef updo
# =============================================================================
# updo — Owloops's "Uptime monitoring CLI tool with
#        alerting and advanced settings" — a Go-based
#        website + API uptime monitor that runs from
#        the terminal (TUI or simple text output) with
#        cross-platform desktop notifications, multi-
#        region AWS Lambda probes, webhook alerts, and
#        Prometheus remote-write metrics export.
#        Designed as a self-hosted alternative to
#        commercial uptime monitoring services
#        (Pingdom, UptimeRobot, StatusCake, BetterStack)
#        for developers + small teams who want full
#        control over their probe infrastructure +
#        notification routing.
#        Distinguishing from uptimerobot-cli (commercial
#        SaaS), checkmk + nagios (heavyweight on-prem
#        monitoring), prometheus-blackbox-exporter
#        (Prometheus-native but no TUI), curl-in-cron
#        (no aggregation), httping (raw ping
#        timing-only), and various StatusCake/Pingdom
#        CLI wrappers by:
#          - LIVE TUI MODE — gizak/termui/v3-based
#            terminal UI showing per-target status +
#            response times + uptime percentage + last
#            check + assertion result in real-time;
#            `--simple` flag falls back to plain-text
#            output for log aggregation / CI use
#          - GEN2BRAIN/BEEEP NOTIFICATIONS — uses
#            gen2brain/beeep for cross-platform desktop
#            notifications (Linux libnotify / D-Bus,
#            macOS osascript / NSUserNotification,
#            Windows toast) when monitored sites fail
#            or recover (this is the headline CLI
#            library that closes Axis 34 on the Go
#            side; see taxonomy notes below)
#          - MULTI-REGION AWS LAMBDA PROBES — `updo aws
#            deploy` deploys AWS Lambda probe functions
#            in multiple regions to simulate global
#            traffic; `updo aws list` shows deployed
#            probes; `updo aws destroy` tears down
#          - WEBHOOK ALERTS — `--webhook-url` +
#            `--webhook-header` send POST notifications
#            to Slack / Discord / PagerDuty / OpsGenie
#            / custom incident systems
#          - PROMETHEUS REMOTE WRITE — `--prometheus-
#            url` exports HTTP request metrics directly
#            to Prometheus remote-write endpoint (e.g.,
#            VictoriaMetrics, Mimir, Cortex) for long-
#            term retention + Grafana dashboards
#          - TOML CONFIG MULTI-TARGET — `--config
#            updo.toml` lets you define many monitored
#            targets in a single file with per-target
#            URL / method / headers / assertion text /
#            refresh / timeout overrides; `--only` +
#            `--skip` filter which targets to monitor
#            this run
#          - HTTP METHOD + BODY — `-X POST -d
#            '{"json":"body"}' -H "Content-Type:
#            application/json"` for API endpoint
#            monitoring beyond simple GET checks
#          - ASSERTION TEXT — `-a "Welcome"` ensures
#            the response body contains the expected
#            text; treats text-absent responses as
#            failure even if HTTP status is 200
#          - SHOULD-FAIL MODE — `--should-fail` inverts
#            success criteria; useful for monitoring
#            that a security-critical endpoint
#            CORRECTLY rejects requests (e.g., expects
#            403 for unauthorized)
#          - SSL SKIP — `--skip-ssl` ignores TLS
#            certificate validation; useful for staging
#            environments with self-signed certs
#          - REDIRECT HANDLING — `-l/--follow-redirects`
#            (default true) follows HTTP redirects;
#            `--accept-redirects` counts 3xx as success
#            without following
#          - JSON LOG OUTPUT — `--log` emits structured
#            JSON logs including request, response, +
#            metrics for downstream log aggregation
#          - CAIO/GO-TDIGEST PERCENTILES — uses go-
#            tdigest for accurate response-time
#            percentile (p50/p95/p99) computation
#            without storing all measurements
#          - COBRA + VIPER STACK — uses spf13/cobra
#            (Axis 1 argparse covered) + spf13/viper
#            (Axis 13 config covered) for the standard
#            Go CLI experience
#        Used by: small teams self-hosting uptime
#        monitoring without paying for SaaS, SREs
#        running incident-response drills, DevOps
#        engineers integrating uptime checks into
#        Prometheus + Grafana stacks, and homelab
#        operators monitoring their personal
#        infrastructure (RPi clusters, NAS, smart-
#        home gateways).
#
# Author:  Owloops organization on GitHub.  License:
#          MIT.  Active development.
# Source:  https://github.com/Owloops/updo
#          https://github.com/Owloops/updo/blob/main/cmd/root/root.go
#          https://github.com/Owloops/updo/blob/main/go.mod
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; documentation in repo
#          README.md + docs/.
# Library: gen2brain/beeep (Go cross-platform desktop
#          notifications — the headline dependency for
#          this completion's axis-companion role; see
#          taxonomy notes below).  Also spf13/cobra
#          (Axis 1 argparse), spf13/viper (Axis 13
#          config), gizak/termui/v3 (TUI rendering),
#          aws/aws-sdk-go-v2 (AWS Lambda multi-region
#          probes), caio/go-tdigest (response-time
#          percentiles), prometheus/protobuf
#          (Prometheus remote-write), golang/snappy
#          (Prometheus remote-write compression).
# License: MIT
